U.S. Options Clearing Corp. Changes Name to OCC as Role Widens

-- B y   J e f f   K e a r n s   a n d   N i n a   M e h t a
-- 
2011-03-16T06:29:32Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-16/u-s-options-clearing-corp-changes-name-to-occ-as-role-widens.html
The  Options Clearing Corp.  changed
its name to OCC, according to a statement from the group which
clears and settles all trading of U.S. exchange-listed equity
derivatives contracts.  The Chicago-based OCC is expanding into markets including
futures, commodities,  securities lending , over-the-counter
equity derivatives and other projects, according to a statement.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Jeff Kearns in New York at 
 jkearns3@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Nick Baker at   nbaker7@bloomberg.net . 